 present have little choice but to rely on food aid for their daily survival, Clapp concludes, the consequences of these political differences are profound.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aInternational Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 70(DE-588)4123819-90(DE-627)1057523390(DE-576)209562935aNahrungsmittelhilfe2gnd  afood crises, food security, contemporary politics of food aid, humanitarian aid, donation, global hunger, emergency assistance, international food aid system, survival, conflict, foreign affairs, donor and recipient.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080146393840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801463938423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801463938/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-060674-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles